---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Chris Lyons"
  description="Learn more about Chris Lyons, a developer, architect, and builder with expertise in modern web technologies."
>
  <div class="section-container-narrow">
    <h1 class="page-title">About Me</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p class="mb-8 text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
        Architect and engineer. I build systems that work, scale, and last.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Background</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        End-to-end builder. Small startups to enterprise systems. Whatever the scale, the goal is
        the same: solve the problem right.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Technical Stack</h2>
      <div class="mb-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-accent mb-2 font-semibold">Frontend</h3>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <li>React, TypeScript</li>
            <li>Astro, Next.js</li>
            <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
            <li>Modern JavaScript (ES2024+)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-accent mb-2 font-semibold">Backend & Infrastructure</h3>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <li>Node.js, Python, Java</li>
            <li>DynamoDB, PostgreSQL, MongoDB</li>
            <li>Docker, Kubernetes</li>
            <li>AWS, Azure, GCP</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">How I Build</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        Code that works today and tomorrow. Here's what matters:
      </p>

      <div class="mb-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Security First</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Input validation, output sanitization, least privilege access. Security is the
            foundation, not a checkbox.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Observability</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Structured logging, distributed tracing, metrics that matter. Know what's happening in
            production before users do.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Reliability</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Circuit breakers, retries with backoff, graceful degradation. Systems fail—design for
            it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Performance</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Sub-second response times, efficient queries, lazy loading where it counts. Fast by
            default.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Cost Optimization</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Right-sized resources, autoscaling, spot instances where safe. Efficient architecture
            scales within budget.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Architecture as Code</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            C4 diagrams generated from source, updated on every commit. Documentation lives with the
            system.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Automated Docs</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            API specs from code, architecture from structure. Generate it, version it, never let it
            drift.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-hover p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Operational Excellence</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            CI/CD pipelines, automated rollbacks, incident retrospectives. Build it, run it, learn
            from it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Signature Card -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <div
          class="border-electric-600/20 dark:border-electric-600/40 dark:to-slate-850 rounded-lg border-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-gray-50 p-6 text-center dark:from-slate-900"
        >
          <p class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
            Every Line Is a Choice
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            Clarity over cleverness. Reliability over shortcuts. Build it right.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
